
@startuml

class ResearchGroup {
  - id: int
  - name: string
  - department: string
  + assignResearcher(researcher: Researcher)
  + reassignLeader(wp: WorkPackage, newLeader: Researcher)
}

class Project {
  - id: int
  - name: string
  - startDate: date
  - endDate: date
  + addWorkPackage(wp: WorkPackage)
}

class WorkPackage {
  - id: int
  - name: string
  - description: string
  - leader: ResearchGroup
  + assignResearcher(researcher: Researcher)
  + reassignLeader(newLeader: ResearchGroup)
}

class Researcher {
  - id: int
  - name: string
  - email: string
  - currentResearchGroup: ResearchGroup
  + assignToWP(wp: WorkPackage)
  + changeResearchGroup(newGroup: ResearchGroup)
}

' Relationships
ResearchGroup "1" -- "0..*" Researcher : belongsTo
Project "1" -- "1.." WorkPackage : contains
WorkPackage "1" -- "0..*" Researcher : hasTeamMembers
Researcher "1" -- "1" ResearchGroup : belongsTo (inverse)
WorkPackage "1" -- "1" ResearchGroup : ledBy

@enduml

### Explanation of the Diagram:

- **ResearchGroup**: Represents a group within a department. Each researcher is assigned to exactly one research group.
- **Project**: A collection of work packages.
- **WorkPackage**: A unit of work under a project. It has a leader (a research group), and multiple researchers can be assigned to it.
- **Researcher**: A person who belongs to a research group and can be assigned to one or more work packages.
- **Relationships**:
  - A `ResearchGroup` can have many `Researchers`.
  - A `Project` has many `WorkPackages`.
  - A `WorkPackage` has a `ResearchGroup` as its leader and can have many `Researchers` assigned to it.
  - A `Researcher` can be assigned to multiple `WorkPackages`, regardless of which group leads them.
  - When a `Researcher` changes groups or a `WorkPackage` leader changes, the assignment records are updated accordingly.

